Along with a decline in economic activity and an increase in unemployment, the most significant drop in foreign direct investment in the last 10 years was also recorded in 2011. According to the Ministry of Finance, between January and June, foreign direct investment amounted to $630,697 in the period from January to June, a decrease of 87.74% compared to $5,143,312 for the same period in the previous year.
